  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-Saving Assistance to Internally Displaced Persons and other Conflict-Affected Populations in Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the aim to the strengthening of capacities, awareness, and direct assistance for a greater protection and wellbeing of the most vulnerableconflict-affected populations in Yemen in a timely and responsive manner, IOM will ensure that :1)Conflict-affected people in Yemen have access to life-saving health assistance; 2) Conflict-affected people in Yemen have access to critical life-saving non-food items (NFI); 3) Conflict-affected people in Yemen have access to safe drinking water, sanitation facilities, and hygiene awareness campaigns; 4) Conflict-affected people in Yemen have access to safe and dignified shelter solutions; 5) Rapid Response Teams are ready to support wheneverneeded within 72 hours; 6) Children in Yemen affected by the stressors related to a protracted situation of war are empowered and better able to react to protection threats.</narrative>
  </description>
